# ============================================
# QUICK SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================
#
# 1. Add PostgreSQL Database:
#    - In Railway project, click "New" → "Database" → "PostgreSQL"
#
# 2. Add Database Reference Variables:
#    - Click your web service → "Variables"
#    - Click "New Variable" → "Add Reference"
#    - Select PostgreSQL service
#    - Add 5 references: DB_HOST, DB_PORT, DB_NAME, DB_USER, DB_PASS
#    - Map them to: PGHOST, PGPORT, PGDATABASE, PGUSER, PGPASSWORD
#
# 3. Add Regular Variables:
#    - Click "New Variable" → "Add Variable"
#    - Copy each variable name and value from above
#    - Required: SENDGRID_API_KEY, SMTP_FROM, SMTP_FROM_NAME
#    - Required: All SG_TMPL_* template IDs
#    - Optional: TWILIO_* variables (if using SMS)
#
# 4. Volume Setup (for file uploads):
#    - Go to service settings → "Volumes"
#    - Click "Add Volume"
#    - Mount path: /var/data/uploads
#    - Size: 1GB (or more as needed)
